      <h2>Full-Service General Contracting Across Maui</h2>
      <p>When you're looking for construction companies on Maui, the options range from large commercial firms to solo handymen with no license. Great General LLC sits in a different category: a small, focused general contracting operation where the owner — Noel — is directly involved in every project from the first site visit through final punch list.</p>

      <p>We hold a Hawaii DCCA B License (General Building Contractor), which is one of the most comprehensive contractor licenses issued in Hawaii. It allows us to self-perform the core trades — carpentry, framing, drywall installation and finishing, interior and exterior demolition, and more. For property owners on Maui, that means a contractor who actually knows what's happening on your job site every day.</p>

      <p>We've been operating on Maui for five-plus years. In that time, we've worked on residential homes from Haiku to Kihei, vacation rental units from Wailea to Ka'anapali, and commercial tenant improvements in Kahului and Wailuku. The island presents unique construction challenges — limited material supply chains, coastal environmental conditions, Maui County's specific permitting process, and the logistical reality of working on an island — and we've navigated all of it firsthand.</p>

