      <h2>Projects We Handle</h2>
      <p>Our general contracting work spans a wide range of project types on Maui:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Residential remodels and additions</strong> — kitchen and bathroom renovations, room additions, garage conversions, ADU construction, and whole-home renovations across Maui's residential communities.</li>
        <li><strong>Vacation rental renovations</strong> — full unit refreshes, ADA compliance upgrades, kitchen and bathroom remodels, flooring replacement, and layout modifications. We understand the rental calendar and work to minimize vacancy time.</li>
        <li><strong>Condominium improvements</strong> — interior renovation work within condo units on Maui, coordinated with HOA requirements and building management rules.</li>
        <li><strong>Commercial tenant improvements</strong> — interior buildouts and remodels for commercial tenants in Kahului, Wailuku, and Kihei. From office renovations to retail buildouts, we handle the permitting and construction management.</li>
        <li><strong>New construction coordination</strong> — for new residential construction projects, we manage subcontractor coordination, permit tracking, inspection scheduling, and construction sequencing.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Hawaii's B License Matters</h2>
      <p>Hawaii's contractor licensing system is structured around the work a contractor is legally authorized to perform. A General Building (B) License authorizes the holder to perform work that is incidental to, or supplementary to, the general construction of a building. In practice, this means we can legally perform the structural and finish work that makes up the bulk of most residential and commercial construction projects.</p>
      <p>Hiring an unlicensed contractor or a contractor performing work outside their license scope creates significant risk: unpermitted work, insurance voidance, difficulty selling or refinancing the property, and no legal recourse if the work is defective. When you hire Great General LLC, you're working with a licensed, insured contractor who operates within the law and pulls permits when required.</p>

      <h2>Maui County Permit Process</h2>
      <p>Maui County's Department of Public Works and Environmental Management handles building permits for all construction in unincorporated Maui County. The permitting process on Maui has specific requirements, review timelines, and inspection sequences that differ from what you may have encountered on the mainland.</p>
      <p>We've been through the Maui County permit process many times across a range of project types. We know which projects require over-the-counter permits, which require full plan review, and how to prepare documentation that moves efficiently through the review process. Permit handling is included in our general contracting scope — it's not an add-on or an afterthought.</p>

      <h2>Serving All Communities on Maui</h2>
      <p>We provide general contracting services across the entire island — Kihei, Wailea, Makena, Lahaina, Ka'anapali, Kapalua, Wailuku, Kahului, Paia, Haiku, Makawao, and surrounding communities. There's no extra travel charge for South Maui or Upcountry projects; Maui is our service area in full.</p>

      <h2>Get a Free On-Site Estimate</h2>
      <p>If you have a construction project on Maui — from a bathroom renovation to a full home remodel to a commercial tenant improvement — <a href="tel:8087954044">call us at (808) 795-4044</a> or <a href="/contact">submit an estimate request online</a>. We'll schedule a free on-site visit, walk through the scope with you, and give you a clear, written estimate. No charge, no obligation, no pressure.</p>
